14/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Parliament will discuss the proposed government reshuffle and the election of new ministers on Monday (March 14th). The new streamlined cabinet led by Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic will have 17 ministries and 21 members. Cvetkovic would take over the role of finance minister in addition to his current duties. Deputy Prime Minister Mladjan Dinkic will be replaced by Verica Kalanovic. Defence Minister Dragan Sutanovac, Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic and Justice Minister Snezana Malovic will keep their posts. (Tanjug, Beta, RTS, B92 - 14/03/11)
